2.11	Diphosponate	Bisphosphonate	Bisphosphonates (also called diphosphonates) are a class of drugs that prevent the loss of bone mass, used to treat osteoporosis and similar diseases. They are called bisphosphonates because they have two phosphonate () groups and are similar in structure to pyrophosphate.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/BisphosStruct.svg/200px-BisphosStruct.svg.png
